We're still trying to locate
the maintenance team, Captain.

149
00:16:02,194 --> 00:16:03,761
No, what is going on outside?

150
00:16:03,762 --> 00:16:05,863
We hear people panicked,
people shouting.

151
00:16:05,864 --> 00:16:08,032
Available personnel must assemble

152
00:16:08,033 --> 00:16:10,435
at the calling point
in parking lot C.

153
00:16:10,436 --> 00:16:13,805
We are soldiers, for Christ's
sake. We can handle it.

154
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:15,807
Please, ma'am, you
need to be patient.

155
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:17,809
No, you need to tell
us what's going on.

156
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:20,011
What gives you the right
to keep it from us?

157
00:16:20,012 --> 00:16:23,247
Yes, ma'am, you'll be out of there
soon. We haven't forgotten you.

158
00:16:23,248 --> 00:16:25,760
We're doing our best.

159
00:16:33,158 --> 00:16:35,169
What?

160
00:16:41,834 --> 00:16:44,268
She knows more than she's
telling us. Did you hear all that?

161
00:16:44,269 --> 00:16:46,440
They'll figure it out.
They'll get us out of here.

162
00:16:52,111 --> 00:16:54,479
Do you know something
that we don't, Sergeant?

163
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:56,560
This had to happen.

164
00:16:58,517 --> 00:17:00,518
It's always "when," not "if."

165
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:02,086
it seems that "when" is now.

166
00:17:02,087 --> 00:17:04,088
What are you talking about?

167
00:17:04,089 --> 00:17:05,857
This.

168
00:17:05,858 --> 00:17:08,259
Them out there.

169
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:10,340
Who?

170
00:17:12,097 --> 00:17:14,177
Well...

171
00:17:20,739 --> 00:17:23,251
Thanks for the insight.

172
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:52,816
I think texts are working.

173
00:18:42,955 --> 00:18:45,729
Come on. Come on.

174
00:18:46,658 --> 00:18:47,896
Come on.

175
00:19:02,274 --> 00:19:04,285
Everything okay, ma'am?

176
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:11,782
Stop breathing like that.

177
00:19:11,783 --> 00:19:14,585
Ma'am.

178
00:19:14,586 --> 00:19:16,791
Stop breathing like that.

179
00:19:21,226 --> 00:19:22,593
Stop it!

180
00:19:22,594 --> 00:19:24,595
- Stop fucking breathing!
- Sir.

181
00:19:24,596 --> 00:19:26,297
Don't you fucking touch me.

182
00:19:26,298 --> 00:19:28,309
I respectfully request
that you calm down.

183
00:19:37,809 --> 00:19:39,582
You need to see this.

184
00:19:45,717 --> 00:19:47,618
The breaking news here

185
00:19:47,619 --> 00:19:50,655
is that a series of explosions
have hit Washington, DC.

186
00:19:50,656 --> 00:19:54,091
I'm here on the ground and this is
still a dangerous situation here.

187
00:19:54,092 --> 00:19:56,861
No one knows if any more
bombs are going to go off.

188
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:58,529
I'm speaking to you on a sat phone

189
00:19:58,530 --> 00:20:02,033
because some kind of
electromagnetic pulse explosion

190
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:03,868
has taken out our camera feed

191
00:20:03,869 --> 00:20:07,104
along with other electronic
systems in a five-mile radius.

192
00:20:07,105 --> 00:20:11,108
I can see in the distance right
now several plumes of smoke.

193
00:20:11,109 --> 00:20:13,711
Those are located, as you
can see in this footage,

194
00:20:13,712 --> 00:20:15,513
right near the Capitol Building.

195
00:20:15,514 --> 00:20:18,015
Homeland Security is saying
the real threat here

196
00:20:18,016 --> 00:20:22,220
is not those bombs but another one
that went off a few miles from here

197
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:24,055
in Brooklines, Maryland.

198
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,790
They're saying that bomb contained

199
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:29,227
radioactive material...
a so-called dirty bomb...

200
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:32,196
and the radiation cloud is
heading right this way.

201
00:20:32,197 --> 00:20:34,832
So we're going to have to
move out at any moment.

202
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:36,734
Civilians are evacuating

203
00:20:36,735 --> 00:20:39,839
and heavy traffic is already building
on routes out of the city...

204
00:20:54,519 --> 00:20:57,121
Let's talk a bit about
everything that happened.

205
00:20:57,122 --> 00:21:02,360
Are there some specific incidents
that trouble you more than others?

206
00:21:02,361 --> 00:21:04,562
Uh, a few of the sergeants...
staff sergeant

207
00:21:04,563 --> 00:21:08,165
was in the front... the front...
the first Humvee.

208
00:21:08,166 --> 00:21:09,834
And we were in the second...

209
00:21:09,835 --> 00:21:13,704
me and my best buddy Pete.

210
00:21:13,705 --> 00:21:16,407
It gets hit with an RPG, just bam!

211
00:21:16,408 --> 00:21:18,409
And it... it tips over.

212
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:21,812
And evidently there might have been,
like, an IED in the road as well.

213
00:21:21,813 --> 00:21:23,814
And the shrapnel shot up and...

214
00:21:23,815 --> 00:21:25,816
and what I think
happened is that it...

215
00:21:25,817 --> 00:21:28,185
it hit the staff sergeant
and just took him out.

216
00:21:28,186 --> 00:21:32,857
I was the next one in
line, so I got out.

217
00:21:32,858 --> 00:21:35,159
A bunch of us got out... Pete.

218
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:40,264
And we decided to try
to get the survivors,

219
00:21:40,265 --> 00:21:42,033
if there were any survivors, out.

220
00:21:42,034 --> 00:21:45,169
And as we got up there,
they started shooting.

221
00:21:45,170 --> 00:21:48,251
And pretty much they were all...
they were shooting from afar.

222
00:21:51,777 --> 00:21:53,477
Answer, God damn it.

223
00:21:53,478 --> 00:21:55,846
Yes, ma'am, we hear you.
Captain, can you please calm...?

224
00:21:55,847 --> 00:21:57,415
Do not tell me to calm down.

225
00:21:57,416 --> 00:21:59,283
We know what's going on out
there. You are gonna tell us

226
00:21:59,284 --> 00:22:01,824
how you're getting us out of here
and when. You understand me?

227
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:05,523
Captain, we've been informed

228
00:22:05,524 --> 00:22:07,825
that a series of bombs
have hit the city.

229
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:13,130
And we have reason to believe
that one of them is a dirty bomb.

230
00:22:13,131 --> 00:22:16,334
Now we're waiting for an
update on wind direction

231
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:19,136
and projected path of
the radiation cloud.

232
00:22:19,137 --> 00:22:22,039
But the city is being evacuated.

233
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:24,875
Ma'am, we really need
to get out of here.

234
00:22:24,876 --> 00:22:26,877
I know, but we've not
been able to locate

235
00:22:26,878 --> 00:22:29,046
the maintenance team responsible
for the elevators yet.

236
00:22:29,047 --> 00:22:30,353
But we are still trying.

237
00:22:32,317 --> 00:22:34,318
Where the hell are they?

238
00:22:34,319 --> 00:22:37,121
We don't know, but I will
continue to try to locate them,

239
00:22:37,122 --> 00:22:39,123
and then we can get
you out, Captain.

240
00:22:39,124 --> 00:22:41,602
Okay, come back to us
as soon as you can.

241
00:22:47,766 --> 00:22:49,427
You need to get out
of here too, right?

242
00:22:52,938 --> 00:22:55,806
My room mate Pete...

243
00:22:55,807 --> 00:22:57,975
he won't understand
what's going on.

244
00:22:57,976 --> 00:23:02,513
He had a piece of
shrapnel from an IED.

245
00:23:02,514 --> 00:23:04,890
You know, about like yea big.

246
00:23:08,053 --> 00:23:09,286
You taking care of him?

247
00:23:09,287 --> 00:23:11,689
He ain't got no family,
so I've been...

248
00:23:11,690 --> 00:23:14,566
I've been looking after him,
you know, since we got back.

249
00:23:19,531 --> 00:23:21,941
It'll be okay. We'll get them safe.

250
00:23:25,604 --> 00:23:29,117
Whoa, Distinguished Service Cross.

251
00:23:31,877 --> 00:23:34,311
You should be proud, soldier.

252
00:23:34,312 --> 00:23:36,619
It's nothing.

253
00:24:02,307 --> 00:24:04,975
- Hey, you need to get a message out?
- That's okay.

254
00:24:04,976 --> 00:24:07,579
Come on, maybe someone
can go get him.

255
00:24:19,324 --> 00:24:21,836
Calm down, Sergeant.

256
00:24:22,761 --> 00:24:24,261
Hey, anyone there?

257
00:24:24,262 --> 00:24:26,263
Yes, ma'am.

